Vice President Joe Biden has announced that Jake Sullivan will serve as his new National Security Advisor. Sullivan previously worked at the State Department as the Director of Policy Planning and Deputy Chief of Staff to Secretary of State Hillary Clinton. Biden praised Sullivan for his intellect, dedication, and experience handling complex foreign policy issues. Sullivan has also worked on Senator Clinton's presidential campaign and served as Chief Counsel to Senator Amy Klobuchar. He has a background in law, having worked as an associate at a law firm and as a clerk for Judge Guido Calabresi and Justice Stephen Breyer. Sullivan graduated from Yale College and earned an M.Phil. in International Relations from Oxford as a Rhodes Scholar. His formal title will be Deputy Assistant to the President and National Security Advisor to the Vice President.